body:
Future

Idk what to call it

summary: Avengers are going to the future

A/n: I will try to get as many of the suggestions in it. This is more like a joking fic. Nothing really serious. Basically a shitpost

Wairnings: none

pairings: none

✧ ✧ ✧

“Scott? What are you doing with the quantum portal?” Hope asks her boyfriend. “Oh there was a small malfunction so I am trying to fix it. I have no idea what I am doing though” he says. “What than you shouldn’t touch it!” Hope runs towards Scott so she could keep him away from the portal. “What going on?”’Steve walks in. “Mr. Lang was messing with the quantum portal” Peter says as he scales of the wall. “Peter? You were there you know how dangerous this is?” Hope says strict. “What- what’s happening?” Tony suddenly apears through to his dad powers. “Peter was here while Scott was working on the quantum portal” Bucky emerges from the shadows. “Yeah. Me and Pete were just hanging out at the ceilings” Clint drops out of the vents. “Can nobody enter like a regular human person” Cap exclaims. “No we can’t” Sam suddenly flies through the door with red wing and Bucky trailing him.

Just infront of the portal Sam makes a sharp turn, Bucky however was a little to late and crashed straight in the portal. The machine started roaring and everyone started in wide eyed shock. Yellow strings start to surround the group of superheroes and suddenly they were gone.

“Where are we?” Tony asks his teammates. “I don’t know” Thor answers. “I think we travelled in time” Scott says. “And what makes you say that?” Clint raises his eyebrows. “Well the paper say it’s 4067” he shows the news to the others. “Oh my god! It’s the Daily Prophet” Peter grabs it and checks the moving pictures. “we should find a way to get back” Natasha states. “Yeez woman when did you get here?” Clint asks. “I’ve been here the entire time” she shrugs. “We should probably check out a museum that might help with getting home” Cap suggests. “Really how?” Tony rolls his eyes. “um,, Mr. Stark I want to go to the museum to maybe they have something about us” Peter pipes. “Let’s go to the museum” Tony walks towards the sign indicating where they should be. “Doesn’t it look weird that we’re in our superhero costumes?” Bucky asks. “Yes it does” Sam says.

“Guys I found it. Let’s just fly there okay?” the ones who can fly all took someone in their arms and Oeter swung with Clint held in his arms like a baby. “It was fairly strange for the citizens since nobody can fly and birds had extinct and planes didn’t exist since the horrible accident of 3418.

When they arrived at the museum they saw a big sign which was litterd with the words The myths of the Avengers. “Lets go there” Peter tucked Tony’s suit. “Sure thing kid” they all walked to the exhibit. “What the-” Clint says, “It says here that we’re all straight” he looks up to the team who starts laughing immediately. They all walk in the direction of there own stand.

“Why do I look like Rapunzel in every picture?” Thor asks his teammates. “You had long blonde hair Mr. Thor your majesty sir” Peter says.

“Okay there is NO WAY they seriously think that the serum turned me into a FISH for seven hunderd years so I could survive under the fucking ice. And why the FUCK are they spelling my name as Stiphin?” Cap exclaims. “So you cursed infront of your teammates” Peter says as he sits on the most nearby chair. “Okay so they have everything wrong but they still have the video’s” ‘Stiphin’ says as he watches them on a big hologram.

“Well, according to this I fucked my way through the entire population of New York and was the father of every second generation superhero? Does that make me Zeus?” Tony furrows his eyebrows. “No Zeus had cool powers.” Sam retorts. “Hahah it says here that your name is Tony Stank” Rhodey laughs. “At least it says that I was the boss” Tony smiles to himself.

“It says here that as a kid I was blind and than Sam came and granted me eyes of his trusty advisor redwing” Clint reads out loud. “Why are these paintings of me naked?? I always wear pants as hulk and Banner” Bruce exclaims.

“Guys,, here it says ‘And, one of the most powerful heroes of all, called himself king of the insects. With eight arms & six eyes and the chosen name of Lord Peterson, this ruler once set an army of poisonous spiders upon his mortal enemy after finding out that she had killed his family and stolen the woman he loved. It is thought that the lands were infested with spiders for years after, as a warning to anyone who attempted to challenge him’ I can’t even pick up a spider without screaming” Peter says.

“Hahah you puny mortals there is written here that I am the god of seduction and that I had an entire army of people that did everthing I wished” Loki says in triomph.

“Hope they think we are real bugs that can transform into humans” Scott says in disgust. “What is written about you Bucky?” Steve asks, as he sees Bucky on the verge of tears. “That eventhough I had rough patches I overcame them and became one of the most loved superheroes” he smiles.

“And what about you Nat?” Tony asks. “It says that I am the godess of strength” she nods her head. “You get to be a god and I have to be some blind kid with -actual hawkeyes???” Clint exclaims. “Yup” Natasha says popping the p.

“Everyone while you were googling yourself Infound a way to go home” Hope says. “Great everyone let’s go” Tony orders. “Let us retrieve to home” Thor booms.

✧ ✧ ✧

Requests are open

summary: Imagine watching the Shape of Water with Loki.  It strikes a cord with him watching the fishman being tortured, called a...
body: Imagine watching the Shape of Water with Loki. It strikes a cord with him watching the fishman being tortured, called a monster, having magic, being called a god and finally falling in love. When the movie is over you can tell Loki is feeling so many emotions that he’s speechless. You run a hot bath for the both of you. In the tub you cuddle up to him and he tells you all his pent emotions.

summary: Comic Book Movie News Websites Attack Fans - Label Them "Sexist" For Saying They Don't Want to See Brie Larson's Captain Marvel
title: Comic Book Movie News Websites Attack Fans - Label Them "Sexist" For Saying They Don't Want to See Brie Larson's Captain Marvel
body:
Comic Book Movie News Websites Attack Fans – Label Them “Sexist” For Saying They Don’t Want to See Brie Larson’s Captain Marvel

Multiple comic book movie news websites including ComicBook.com and ComicBookMovie.com attacked comic book fans because they expressed that they do not plan to see Brie Larson’s Captain Marvel when it comes into theaters.

ComicBook.com would blatantly lie in the headline stating, “Captain Marvel Is Already Being Review Bombed on Rotten Tomatoes.” (Archive link: http://archive.is/rsntu)  The movie…
